---
title: One-Pan Mushroom Gnocchi with Sun-Dried Tomatoes & Parmesan Cream Sauce
description: How deep is your love? We may never know the answer to this question but we can tell you that the flavors in this sauce are as deep as the ocean. That’s thanks to the savory complexity of mushrooms, sun-dried tomatoes, and Parmesan cheese in a decadent cream sauce. Instead of boiling, the gnocchi are pan-seared until crisp, adding great texture to the dish. The all-in-one meal is finished with peas, which add a little sweetness... Talk about depth of flavor!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/one-pan-mushroom-gnocchi-97bfbdad.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/one-pan-mushroom-gnocchi-61a78b961265154bb377986d-73962c74.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pan-mushroom-gnocchi-61a78b961265154bb377986d
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Italian
nutrition:
  calories: 710 kcal
  fat: 39 g
  saturated fat: 22 g
  carbohydrates: 74 g
  sugar: 15 g
  protein: 17 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1960 mg
course: main course
---

Wash and dry produce.

Finely chop @sun-dried tomatoes{1.5%ounce}. Trim and thinly slice @cremini mushrooms{4%ounce}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add sun-dried tomatoes and mushrooms. Cook, stirring occasionally, until mushrooms are browned and softened, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Turn off heat; let pan cool slightly. Transfer everything to a #medium bowl{}.

Melt @butter{2%tablespoon} in same pan over medium heat. Cook, stirring, until foamy, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @gnocchi{8.8%ounce} and stir to coat. Cook, undisturbed, until browned and crisp on one side, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Stir gnocchi and cook, undisturbed, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Add @veggie stock concentrate{1} and a splash of @water{}; stir to coat. Cook until water has evaporated, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Remove pan from heat. Transfer gnocchi to a second medium bowl.

Heat pan used for gnocchi over medium heat. Add @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, half the @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} (save the rest for serving), @italian seasoning{1%teaspoon}, @butter{1%tablespoon}, and @water{1/4%cup}. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce is combined and simmering, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Reduce heat to medium low. Stir gnocchi, sun-dried tomatoes and mushrooms, and @peas{4%ounce} into pan with sauce. Cook until gnocchi is coated and peas are warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide gnocchi between #bowls{}. Top with remaining parmesan and serve.

> Instead of boiling, pan-searing the gnocchi until crisp adds great texture to the dish.
> Peas add a little sweetness... Talk about depth of flavor!